python version : 2.7 
opencv version : 3.1
requires numpy python module

Setup Instructions for CSU computer labs. Run the following commands before
 running python.

export PYTHONPATH="/usr/local/OpenCV/lib/python2.7/site-packages:PYTHONPATH"
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH="/usr/local/ffmpeg/lib:LD_LIBRARY_PATH"



Usage: AlgorithmRunAndEval.py <input video> [flags..] [-t <startFrame> ]
-----------------------------------------------
Argument descriptions:
       -e <ground truth video> -- evaluate the results. Turn on evaluation mode.
       -s  -- silent; run without console output.
       -Si -- show input frames.
       -So -- show overlay. Puts boxes around detected objects.
       -t <startFrame> -- start running after <startFrame> frames.
EVALUATION MODE:
       -n  -- no csv output.
       -Sd -- show diff frame.
       -St -- show truth frame.

Argument Notes:

The -e argument must be given for any of the evaluation mode arguments to have
an effect. Regardless, the program will not warn if evaluation mode arguments
are given.

Here are some examples of how to run the program. Make sure python 2.7 is used with OpenCV 3.1.

Example 1 -- Processing only

python AlgorithmRunAndEval.py assets\PETS2006\input.avi


Example 2 -- Processing and evaluation. The program also displays the
 differences and shows object detection boxes.

python AlgorithmRunAndEval.py assets\PETS2006\input.avi -e assets\P
ETS2006\gt.avi -Sd -So